    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite identified gaps in several credibility factors, the assessment team determined that the combination of Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, turbulence model sensitivity analysis, and hemolysis benchmark comparison provides sufficient evidence for the intended regulatory submission under the Low assurance level designation. Remaining gaps are documented as known limitations requiring resolution prior to any higher-assurance resubmission. The mesh independence study and associated verification activities are recorded as complete in the activity registry.",
